stored_items.text:
Caring for Chrome, PVD & other Special Finishes
-  The ideal cleaning technique is to always blot dry any water from metal surfaces. Allowing water to
evaporate on metal will form water deposits. It is important to use a dabbing action to dry metal,
not  a  rubbing  action.  Cleaning  with  a  damp  sponge  &  buff  drying  should  keep  your  faucet
looking beautiful.
-  Most toilet cleaning products have high acidic content which can damage the finish; hence they
should not be used to clean chrome finishes or PVD Finishes.
-  If limescale has built up on your product do not attempt to chip this off as this could damage the
protective  lacquer  &  lead  to  further  damage.  Several  applications  of  lemon  juice  (not  a
concentrate) or white vinegar, followed by a thorough rinsing with clean water will slowly help to
remove it.
Caring for Artisanal Wash Basins & Special-Finish Ceramic Sanitaryware
-  Do not place the product outdoors or in direct exposure to sun light.
-  Stainless-steel may discolour if left in contact with salts or acids for extended periods.
-  Residues of toiletries such as liquid soaps, shower gels, shampoos, hair dyes, perfumes, lipstick,
after shave & nail varnish can also cause damage if not wiped up right away, this can allow the
acids to react & eat away at the calcium carbonate in stone wash basins, creating permanent
markings.
-  Wherever Rose Gold/ Gold/ Silver/ Matt Finishes/ Marble Finishes or any other type of special
finishes are used on ceramic products, use only warm water to clean & then dry with a soft cloth.
Ensure  that  specialized  cleaners  are  only  applied  to  the  specific  area  &  do  not  meet  other
materials that could be affected by it.
-  If  you  wish  to  use  common  cleaning  products  on  Toilets  with  Rose  Gold/  Gold/  Silver/  Matt
Finishes, dilute the cleaning product with water. Do not allow the cleaning product to sit on the
product, rinse immediately. Restrict use of cleaning product to only the inside of the toilet bowl
& DO NOT allow the cleaning product to have contact with external surface finishes or the toilet
seat. DO NOT use such cleaners on Wash Basins.
* All PRODUCT PHOTOS ARE INDICATIVE ONLY.
stored_items.name: Caring for Chrome, PVD & other Special Finishes
stored_items.source: Aquant Price List Vol. 14 Feb. 2025 - Low Res Searchable

stored_items.text:
Care & Maintenance – An Overview
-  To  ensure  your  Aquant  product  performs  &  gives  many  years  of  use,  please  follow  these
recommendations carefully, as any damages resulting from poor maintenance are not covered
under warranty.
-  Most products can be cleaned with warm water, a mild soap & a clean, soft cloth.
-  It is not required to use any abrasive cleaning pads, wire wool or micro-fibre cloths to clean the
product. Avoid a vigorous cleaning action.
-  Abrasive  or  strong  cleaning  products  containing  ammonia,  bleaches,  alcohol,  dyes,  acids
(hydrochloric, formic, phosphorus, chlorine or acetic) will be detrimental to the product finish.
-  If using a spray cleaner, apply the cleaning agent onto a soft cloth, never directly spray onto the
product as the cleaner may enter gaps & openings & cause damage.
-  Residues of toiletries such as liquid soaps, shower gels, shampoos, hair dyes, perfumes, lipstick,
after shave & nail varnish can also cause damage, carefully clean these using the methods above.
-  If a specialized cleaner is required, always follow the instructions provided on the cleaning product,
this would include application & dosage.
-  Always test the cleaning agent on an inconspicuous area before applying to the whole surface, do
not  allow  the  cleaner  to  remain  on  the  product  for  an  extended  period.  After  cleaning,  rinse
thoroughly with clean water.
-  We would not recommend the mixing of different cleaning agents. After cleaning, dry with a soft
cloth.
